systemRestartDate.description: The date (YY*104+MM*102+DD) when the agent has started a new Z matrix.

systemRestartTime.description: The time (HH*104+MM*102+SS) when the agent has started a new Z matrix.

systemKeySize.description: The number of bytes (K) of each generated key.

systemIntervalUpdate.description: The number of milliseconds of the updating interval of the internal Z matrix.

systemMaxNumberOfKeys.description: The maximum number of generated keys that are still valid.

systemKeysTimeToLive.description: The number of seconds of the TTL of the generated keys.

configMasterKey.description: The master double key M with at least K*2 bytes in size.

configFirstCharOfKeysAlphabet.description: The ASCII code of the first character of the alphabet used in the keys (default=33).

configCardinalityOfKeysAlphabet.description: The number of characters (Y) in the alphabet used in the keys (default=94).

dataNumberOfValidKeys.description: The number of elements in the dataTableGeneratedKeys.

dataTableGeneratedKeys.description: A table with information from all created keys that are still valid.

keyId.description: The identification of a generated key.

keyValue.description: The value of a generated key (K bytes/characters long).

KeyRequester.description: The identification of the manager/client that initially requested the key.

keyExpirationDate.description: The date (YY*104+MM*102+DD) when the key will expire.

keyExpirationTime.description: The time (HH*104+MM*102+SS) when the key will expire.

keyVisibility.description: 0 - Key value is not visible; 1 - key value is only visible to the requester; 2 - key value is visible to anyone.
